24 WHEREAS, after natural disasters such as hurricanes, tornadoes, and floods,
25 following school shooting events, and during the course of public
26 emergencies, recovery must be prioritized as a long-term process rather than
27 an immediate, short-term response process; and
28
29 WHEREAS, states, school districts, and postsecondary institutions have
30 focused on crisis prevention and management, but may not have the capacity to
31 provide sustained support for students, teachers, communities, and even their
32 own counselors during the recovery stage following a crisis; and
33
34 WHEREAS, rural schools and postsecondary institutions in particular tend to
35 have fewer counselors and limited access to additional counseling resources;
36 and
