1 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE NINETY-FIFTH GENERAL
2 ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
3
4 THAT the Southern Regional Education Board, in close collaboration with
5 governors' offices, state education agencies, local schools, and
6 postsecondary institutions, will complement existing school and school
7 district crisis management efforts by focusing on long-term healing and
8 psychological resilience by deploying counselors with specialized training to
9 schools and postsecondary institutions in extreme need.
10
11 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED THAT the Southern Regional Education Board will hire a
12 coordinator for the Crisis Recovery Support Network and cover travel costs
13 for counselors during the training and deployment processes.
14
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED THAT to meet the urgent need for a coordinated,
16 region-wide effort to provide a consistent, long-term counseling capacity
17 that is ready to deploy immediately after a crisis, the House of
18 Representatives support the Southern Regional Education Board Crisis Recovery
19 Support Network.
20
21 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED THAT upon adoption, a copy of this resolution shall be
22 provided to the Southern Regional Education Board by the Chief Clerk of the
23 House of Representatives.
